1
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,100
It didn't work because
Kentucky is different.

2
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:09,200
Kentucky is different from California
and New York. The patients are different...

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:13,500
...from Brazil and London. The model was built
on 400 million patients across the world.

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:17,400
What we needed was a model built
on Kentucky patients...

5
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:21,141
...with Kentucky data,
with Kentucky problems.

6
00:00:21,141 --> 00:00:25,500
The Cabinet for Health and Family Services
has a state-university partnership...

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:30,001
...where you can propose getting access
to state data - super valuable data.

8
00:00:30,001 --> 00:00:33,461
Now it's up to us to figure out how to use
that data to make healthcare better.

9
00:00:33,461 --> 00:00:36,500
The final one is essentially
cancer screening.

10
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:40,500
Can we get ahold of Medicaid claims data
and identify patients eligible for screening...

11
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:44,800
...whether it's colon cancer, lung cancer,
or cervical cancer...

12
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:49,621
...find those patients, and deploy
similar software to reach out to them?

13
00:00:49,621 --> 00:00:53,000
We think we can design an AI agent
that walks you through the process...

14
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,600
...and schedules your appointment
at the same time...

15
00:00:56,600 --> 00:01:00,400
...so you don't have to take the onus
on yourself of calling your doctor...

16
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,600
...and trying to get a colonoscopy.
We can do it automatically...

17
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,041
...bring you in, and make sure we are caring
for the people of Kentucky.

18
00:01:06,041 --> 00:01:09,300
We don't want California.
We don't want New York.

19
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,500
We want Kentucky's data
so we can better impact Kentuckians.

20
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,700
We want this to be
a dynamic conversation...

21
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,600
...about what we can do to streamline
and provide better access to data...

22
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,300
...more quickly. Whatever we need to do
on our side...

23
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:23,841
...we want to be a good partner.
